24:37.117 --> 24:43.707
geophysical side of things in the deep oceans. It 
still does to some extent. I don't think our

24:46.831 --> 24:50.316
revolution has stopped yet, really. Because now 
we're working on the problems of understanding

24:50.337 --> 24:58.228
the driving forces associated with plate 
tectonics. What makes it go? And we know very

25:00.311 --> 25:01.994
little about it right now. And we're now 
developing some long, deep penetrating

25:06.901 --> 25:18.680
experiments, one of which is this 
electromagnetic induction studies that I'm

25:06.901 --> 25:18.680
starting to get into, to learn about the depth 
structure of the plates and beneath the plates.

25:18.980 --> 25:21.023
What's the material beneath the plates like? How 
does it distribute in space and over the motions?

25:26.532 --> 25:27.293
