25:31.201 --> 25:38.711
oceanography? That'll be one direction of 
oceanography. I think we're going to see several

25:41.415 --> 25:45.020
directions in oceanography over the next few 
years. I think it's perhaps like the

25:45.060 --> 25:52.330
proliferation of the field itself. We're going to 
see several major directions in oceanography.

25:56.095 --> 25:56.736
What are they? Well, one is associated with the 
ocean waters themselves. The physical

26:00.796 --> 26:20.310
oceanographers are sort of having a revolution by 
themselves right now in terms of understanding

26:00.796 --> 26:20.310
the details of the circulating patterns of 
currents in the oceans and the time scales of the

26:00.796 --> 26:20.310
circulations and the flow of energy, sort of the 
climate in the ocean, so to speak, and the way it

26:00.796 --> 26:20.310
interacts with the climate in the atmosphere. I 
think there's a lot of evidence now that the

26:21.421 --> 26:31.661
oceans' distribution of temperatures and ocean 
waters controls what happens over the

26:21.421 --> 26:31.661
continents. Yes. To a large extent, you probably 
