27:07.138 --> 27:14.206
Galapagos, are only a few thousand years old. And 
here we have new creatures that have probably been

27:14.226 --> 27:22.895
developed there in this period of a few thousand 
years that don't exist elsewhere outside of those

27:14.226 --> 27:22.895
areas. How did they develop? Where did they come 
from? How do they get introduced? How do they live?

27:27.943 --> 27:30.206
What do they live on down there? There's a lot of 
theories going around right now about sulfur

27:30.226 --> 27:38.297
reducing bacteria and how they contribute to the 
food chain at the seafloor from these vent areas.

27:39.699 --> 27:51.214
It may be very localized, but they may have some 
long ranging aspects or implications for the

27:39.699 --> 27:51.214
development of sea life in the ocean. I don't know. 
