27:52.968 --> 27:56.493
think probably will be taught. And then in our 
field, in geological oceanography, I think the

27:57.274 --> 28:07.827
big push is going to be to understand the driving 
forces behind plate tectonics. What are the

28:07.847 --> 28:10.451
deeper motions that are going on? How fast are 
they? How are they distributed? Do we have big

28:13.074 --> 28:15.577
convection cells under the Earth? Where are they? 
What is their time scale? What drives these

28:21.740 --> 28:24.502
motions in the air? Is it heat coming from the 
interior that drives them? If so, why? Where are

28:31.028 --> 28:32.649
the heat sources in the air? These will be 
difficult problems to get at. We may not be able to

28:35.692 --> 28:41.117
answer them unambiguously because we can't get 
down there and sample things. 100 kilometers

28:41.137 --> 28:43.659
down, how are we going to sample it? But the tools we 
have are geophysical. Heat flow,

28:47.202 --> 28:50.785
electromagnetic, seismic, All of these indirect 
methods are going to be the ways in which we learn

28:51.153 --> 29:01.867
about this, and I suspect I'm going to be involved 
with that probably for the rest of my career here in

28:51.153 --> 29:01.867
oceanography. So, in a sense, my early heat flow 
work is being generalized into a more broader

29:01.887 --> 29:12.540
geophysical description of how the Earth works. 
I've been studying it in the oceans, peripherally

29:13.482 --> 29:20.130
on the continents, but I think that's... the 
relationship we see now. And we want to tie the

29:22.230 --> 29:25.918
oceans and the continents together when we make 
this kind of a study. How do the continental masses

29:26.739 --> 29:33.974
react to these sea floor spreading forces that are 
going on? It may turn out that a lot of the activity

29:39.196 --> 29:46.908
or organization of research in the oceans will be 
now applied to the continents. The continents are

29:47.309 --> 29:55.301
much more difficult to understand in many ways, 
even though we're living right on top of them and

29:47.309 --> 29:55.301
have access to them. So it may be that many of these 
geophysical methods, big geophysical programs,

29:55.321 --> 30:04.495
can now be applied to continental areas to 
understand the deep structure there.

